<span id="freeTextContainer12207591405920586361">This is my first Rollins and I have to say this... &quot;Have mercy&quot;(to be read Jesse Katsopolis style). This thrilling page-turner grips you hard and doesn&apos;t let go. If you&apos;re going to have insomnia, or a long flight journey ahead of you, this is one heck of a book to have handy. <br/><br/>This beast of a book reads like a movie - an Indiana Jones meets Avatar with CGI of amazing proportions. It ticked quite a few of the right boxes for me:<br/>1. Well researched information - The jungle description and the wilder</span>
  <span id="freeText12207591405920586361" style="display:none">This is my first Rollins and I have to say this... "Have mercy"(to be read Jesse Katsopolis style). This thrilling page-turner grips you hard and doesn't let go. If you're going to have insomnia, or a long flight journey ahead of you, this is one heck of a book to have handy. <br /><br />This beast of a book reads like a movie - an Indiana Jones meets Avatar with CGI of amazing proportions. It ticked quite a few of the right boxes for me:<br />1. Well researched information - The jungle description and the wilderness is so detailed, that I can only imagine the amount of study Rollins put into writing Amazonia. I found the scientific aspects quite interesting and it usually didn't go too far over my head, so points for that.<br />2. Atmospheric setting - Green, dark, wet and, at night, creepy as all hell.<br />3. Interesting protagonists - Even though Nathan Rand was the lead, I enjoyed the characters Kelly and Tor-Tor so much more. <br />4. Creature feature - The chimeras... what the... <br />5. Scares - Plenty of them.<br />6. Plot Twists - Loved the big reveal. Yep, didn't see THAT coming. Slow clap.<br /><br />For the most part, I did find myself enjoying the story and read with my mental- mouth wide open. And in all seriousness, I have to call it a 'fun' adventure buuut... that's all it was for me - Fun - and I wanted it to be so much more. My complaints with the book are few and far between, but they're there. I thought some of the characters (Anna, Kouwe) could have been more fleshed out, and that some other characters (Waxman, Rangers) were not given the credit they deserved. Rand filled the screen. I had to stop myself from rolling my eyes when he saved the day - all day, every day, while everyone else looked on helplessly (and this includes army rangers !!!). And I thought Favre's reasons for desiring vengeance was a little too.. meh? <br /><br />However, the adrenaline-filled pace quite made up for the shortcomings, and I'm glad I started out on this treasure-hunt-type jungle journey. 4 Stars.</span>
