  <span id="freeText17186088700184441417" style="display:none"> <br /><br />⬇️What's your favourite jungle mystery book?<br /> <br />"An unexamined life is not worth living"_ James Rollins (Amazonia)<br /><br />I was expected to read about normal and made up weird animals when I saw the title "Amazonia". As I am studying Animal Husbandry, what else can I think of? And  I always liked zoology over botany. After killing my high expectations, James Rollins shoved me with plants! Don't get me wrong, I loved the way plants were mentioned here. This was just brilliant. I liked the wildly interesting botany facts. The plot was amazing. I love mysterious sci-fi adventures and this book was full of it.<br /><br /><br />This book was about the mystery queen, Amazon. Obviously, it had huge potential and James Rollins didn't leave a stone to make it good. The twists were just crazy. I was amazed at the secrets of the Amazon. History lessons and interesting scientific facts are mixed in with cool story. Now I am going to read all James Rollins. <br /><br />Here the main protagonist's name is also Nathan. This time it is Nathan Rand. And I guess I have a little crush on this Nathan as well🙈🥱 Books are making me gross these days🤦‍♀️ Tell me about your favourite character's name. <br /><br />I am giving it a nice 5/5🌟<br /><br />Highly recommended! </span>
